==English==

===Etymology===

From the concept of [[divide|dividing]] a group of objects into subgroups of [[even]] size.

===Adjective===

# (''mathematics'') Leaving no [[remainder]] when divided by.
#: ''15 is evenly divisible by 3, but 16 isn't.''
# (''mathematics'') Technically ''n'' is evenly divisible by ''d'' (written ''d''|''n'') if there exists an [[integer]] ''q'' such that ''n'' = ''dq''.